HEADWORD: Bordello
<hw>Bor*del"lo</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>bordel</ets>, orig.
a little hut, OF. <ets>borde</ets> hut, cabin, of German origin, and
akin to E. <ets>board</ets>,<pos>n.</pos>See. <er>Board</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A brothel; a bawdyhouse; a house devoted to
prostitution.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>B. Jonson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

